.IPFSphere(1)
.SH NAME
.IPFSphere \- decentralised chat using IPFS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ipfsphere.sh
[\-h]
[\-v]
[\-r]
[\-s]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IPFSphere is a decentralised chat application that utilizes the InterPlanetary File System (IPFS) for communication. It provides a command-line interface for interacting with the chat channels.
.PP
.IPFSphere supports the following options:
.TP
.B \-h
Display help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-v
Display version information and install update if available.
.TP
.B \-r
Reset IPFSphere, deleting all data including messages and certificates.
.TP
.B \-s
Shutdown IPFSphere by stopping the IPFS daemon.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.IP
The following functions are available in IPFSphere:
.TP
.B version
Displays the version information of the IPFSphere script. If an update is available, it prompts the user to update the script.
.TP
.B help
Displays the help information, including the usage and available options of the IPFSphere script.
.TP
.B init
Initializes the IPFS environment and starts the IPFS daemon if necessary. It also enables the required IPFS configuration for IPFSphere.
.TP
.B config
Configures the user's nickname and generates the RSA keypair for the user. It publishes the public key and saves the nickname for future use.
.TP
.B mainwindow
Opens the main chat window where the user can select and interact with different chat channels. It subscribes to the saved channels and displays the messages in each channel.
.TP
.B addchannel
Prompts the user to enter a new channel name and adds it to the list of channels. It subscribes to the new channel and starts the refresh service for that channel.
.TP
.B channelwindow
Opens a specific chat channel window where the user can view and write messages. It displays the messages in the channel and allows the user to publish new messages.
.TP
.B sign_message
Signs a message with the user's private key and returns the signed message.
.TP
.B verify_message
Verifies the signature of a message using the provided public key and returns the verification result.
.TP
.B timestamp_to_date
Converts a UNIX timestamp to a human-readable date format.
.TP
.B date_to_timestamp
Converts a date string to a UNIX timestamp.
.TP
.B process_channel_data
Processes the data received from a chat channel. It checks if the data is already processed, verifies the signature, and adds the messages to the respective channel files.
.TP
.B refresh_service
Continuously refreshes the chat channels by processing new data. It runs in the background and ensures that new messages are displayed in real-time.
.TP
.B request_resend
Sends a resend request to a chat channel, requesting a synchronization of messages. It notifies other participants to resend the messages from a specific date.
.TP
.B handle_resend_request
Handles a resend request by synchronizing the messages from a chat channel. It retrieves the messages within the requested timeframe and publishes them to the channel.
